Name: CM PRESSURE DUMP
checklistText:
CM Pressure Dump

Note:
	The following needs to be off or isolated to prevent
	unnecessary O2 usage:
		EMER CAB PRESS sel - OFF
		PRESSURE SUIT CIRCUIT - isolated from cabin

	a.	Using Cab Press Relf Vlv

Panel 2:
		CAB FAN (both) - OFF (verify)
Panel 7:
		DIRECT O2 vlv - close (CW)

Panel 325:
		CAB PRESS RELF vlv (2) - DUMP
			(safety latch off)
Panel 2:
			CAB PRESS ind - 3.0-3.25 psia
Panel 325:
		CAB PRESS RELF vlv (2) - BOOST/ENTR
Panel 2:
		O2 FLOW ind - ≈0.24 lb/hr
		SUIT PRESS ind - 3.5-4.0 psia
Panel 325:
		CAB PRESS RELF vlv (2) - DUMP
Panel 2:
		CAB PRESS ind - 0.0 psia
			(within 6 min)
Panel 325:
		CAB PRESS RELF vlv (2) - NORM
			(safety latch on)




		
	b.	Using Side Hatch Cab Press Dump Vlv

Panel 2:
		CAB FAN (both) - OFF (verify)
Panel 351:
		EMER CAB PRESS sel - OFF
Panel 326:
		REPRESS PKG vlv - OFF

		If lone crewman oper
			REPRESS PKG vlv - FILL

Panel 601:
		REPRESS O2 vlv - CLOSE
Panel 7:
		DIRECT O2 vlv - close (CW)
			(verify)
Side hatch:
		CAB PRESS DUMP vlv - open
			(CCW - one turn)
Panel 2:
			CAB PRESS ind - 3.0-3.25 psia
Side hatch:
		CAB PRESS DUMP vlv - close
			(CW)
Panel 2:
			O2 FLOW ind - <0.5 lb/hr
			SUIT PRESS ind - 3.5-4.0 psia
Side hatch:
		CAB PRESS DUMP vlv - open
			(CCW)
Panel 2:
		CAB PRESS ind - ≈0 psia
Side hatch:
		CAB PRESS DUMP vlv - close
			(CW)

Steps.Text: Wait for CABIN PRESS to reach 3.25
